      {
        "id": "bc0d8611469c98fa3100335b823979e402716f61",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1677,
          "name": "Daniel Cruz",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dc443y@att.com",
          "username": "dc443y"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-03 17:34:47.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nDo you think there should be some renaming now that some of the older versions are removed? For example, renaming \"ControlLoopEventManager2\" and \"ControlLoopOperationManager2\" to remove the \"2\". Also \"controller-frankfurt\" and \"feature-controlloop-frankfurt\" to \"controller-usecases\" and \"feature-controlloop-usecases\"?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "288ab1e25c09cdee03aefe49e71936e1b7ead43f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-03 18:43:55.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n> \n> Do you think there should be some renaming now that some of the older versions are removed? For example, renaming \"ControlLoopEventManager2\" and \"ControlLoopOperationManager2\" to remove the \"2\". Also \"controller-frankfurt\" and \"feature-controlloop-frankfurt\" to \"controller-usecases\" and \"feature-controlloop-usecases\"?\n\nGood question.  I was going to do that, but am actually planning some re-work, simplifying the Manager classes so all they do is queue up the results, moving all of the control back into rules.  With that in mind, I will probably reuse the original names for the revised rules/classes.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "e870fbbff060ffc6fc8af100c8392c51cb809fd7",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-03 19:10:27.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-2\n\nToo soon to rename frankfurt controller - we do want to be able to do a release with all the tech debt leftover from frankfurt. Not sure if this is premature here to do this.\n\nWhat is the plan to get rid of m2? That should be worked on immediately.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "c474cff699e06c0280f461061cc17d13499acc44",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-03 19:35:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2: Code-Review-2\n> \n> Too soon to rename frankfurt controller - we do want to be able to do a release with all the tech debt leftover from frankfurt. Not sure if this is premature here to do this.\n> \n> What is the plan to get rid of m2? That should be worked on immediately.\n\nNot sure what the objection is.  This leaves the frankfurt controller as is; it only removes the usecases controller.  Not ready to do that yet?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
